      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "🔴 Red Team Phases",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "Reference: MITRE ATT&CK Framework",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "1. Reconnaissance      → Gather intelligence (passive & active)\n2. Initial Access      → Gain a foothold (phishing, web vulns, exposed services)\n3. Execution           → Run payloads on the target system\n4. Persistence         → Maintain access across reboots and credential changes\n5. Privilege Escalation → Move from low-priv to SYSTEM/root/domain admin\n6. Defense Evasion     → Avoid detection by AV, EDR, SIEM\n7. Credential Access   → Dump hashes, tokens, tickets\n8. Lateral Movement    → Pivot to other hosts in the network\n9. Collection          → Find and stage data of interest\n10. Exfiltration       → Move data out of the network\n11. Impact             → Achieve the operation's objective",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
